18:
*pant* *pant* What's happening?
We just came for a pickup!
26: I'll be your next opponent, kid.
29: Why is the Gaea Navy after us?!
33:
Oh, there'll be plenty of time for talk
later.
40:
All we want to know is where the
Crimson Blades are. That's not too
much to ask for, is it?
42:
Pirates, eh? They'll turn their back on
the world, but they won't turn on
each other.
44:
Colonel Selene. Think you can
squeeze more outta this
interrogation?
46:
Well, Admiral. Sweet-talking was
always my specialty rather than
yours, wasn't it?
48:
Hah. Then work your magic,
sugarcake.
52:
Relax. Your little friends got away,
you know.
54:
Hah... That brought some color back
into your cheeks. Do you treasure
your friends, kid?
56:
I like a man that can treat people
right... And, to tell the truth, I've been
your admirer from the very start.
57:
You used the World Flipper to help
the Crimson Blades escape, then
came drifting back like nothing
happened. You're quite a catch...
60: And I won't let you slip away.
70:
I know your future. And it branches
in one of two directions.
71:
First direction. We take you back to
Navy headquarters, where you'll be
tried and interrogated.
72:
We'll be humane about it, of course.
But as long as you keep those lips
sealed, we keep you sealed behind
bars.
74:
Second direction. You tell us
everything you know.
75:
Sell us your friends' information, and
buy your freedom.
83:
I knew you'd say that. I don't find
either option attractive myself.
84:
At this very moment, those are the
only two paths open to you. But if
you're feeling up to it...
86: So it begins. Look out the window.
93:
This vessel is disguised as a shabby
merchant's ship.
94:
And THEY think it's to hide
moneybags and baubles.
102:
Of course, they'd never attack if they
thought this was one of the Navy's
state-of-the-art destroyers. Not
unless they're eager to win a date
with Davy Jones.
104: But you know, miracles DO happen.
114: Stay quiet and do as I say.
133:
And now, we've just blasted open
the third path.
135:
To the Navy, you just died in that
explosion. But to me...
144: I did say I admired you.
153:
This world's on the brink of
destruction, and you and your little
band of world-hoppers are what's
gonna tip the scale. But the
government's not gonna publicize
that.
155:
Oh, they aren't plotting anything.
They just can't see what's at stake,
can't get off their asses, and can't
be bothered to take responsibility.
157: Sounds boring, if you ask me.
164:
You're too complex of a toy for those
old farts to play with. But I'd know
how to press your buttons.
166:
Come on. We don't have time for
your gaping. If you've got any sort of
backbone, follow me. I know a place
you can hide.
171: I don't mind walking into danger.
173:
And I'm open to working with you. It
sure beats being hunted.
182: But I carve my own path!
188:
So next time we meet, we're friends,
right?
195: Kid's gunning after my own heart.
